{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script aims to reproduce the folder separation in a way Logic X does it.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Draw separator on folder track\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script aimes to provide a mechanism similar to the one in LogicProX to separate folders in the Arrange View.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Options\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Actually you have to customize your preferences directly into the script.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b {\f1 TRACK_HEIGHT}} This {\b MUST} be {\b AT LEAST} 2 pixels higher than the size defined in Preferences > Apparence > Media > "Hide labels for items when item take lane height is less than". You also have to uncheck "draw labels above items, rather than within items" {\i Default value is {\b {\f1 28}}} but I got better result with 20pixels.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Default 6 and dafault 5 theme TRACK_HEIGHT=25.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 25 Also works with Jane, Funktion.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab iLogic V2 = 28\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab iLogic V3 = 24\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Flat Madness and CubeXD= 22\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b {\f1 TRACK_COLOR_SINGLE}} Do you want all the item folder to get the same color ? Otherwise, default folder track color will be used. {\i Default is {\b {\f1 0}}}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b {\f1 TRACK_COLOR}} Use RGB color code. {\i Default is {\b {\f1 \{111,121,131\}}}}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b {\f1 TRACK_COLOR_DARKER_STEP}} This is the amount of darkness yo uwant to apply to default track color. 0 means NO darkness. {\i Default is {\b {\f1 25}}}\par}
